2. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the application of cyber-physical systems in the healthcare domain, which has implications for society. 

3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper discusses the security models used in the proposed architecture, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security. 

4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the computation core of the proposed architecture, which involves distributed computing and resource scheduling. 

5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the architecture of the proposed system, which involves software engineering principles such as real-time scheduling and resource management.
